Program: Discovery
Title: Alf Adams
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01yy0wg
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 25 May 2014
Alf Adams FRS, physicist at the University of Surrey, had an idea on a beach in the mid-eighties that made the modern internet, CD and DVD players, and even bar-code readers possible. You probably have half a dozen 'strained-layer quantum well lasers' in your home. Image credit: Alf Adams, BBC Copyright Show less